g NeIlis Nepotes.-That is. Ui Nestl, com- monly called Hy-Neill, or the descendants of Niall of the Niue Hostages. The sons of this monareh by his first wife were Laeghaire, St. Patriek's contemporary, and Conall Crimthaun, grandfather of Dermait Mac Cerbhail, men- tioned above in cap. 36. whose descendants oc- cupied Meath, and were, from their position, styled the southern Hy Neill. By his second wife he had Eoghan, aucestor of the Cenel Eoghain, who gave name to Tyrone and [111511- owen. and were in after times represented by the O'Neill family3 Conall Gulban, aucestor of the Cinel Conaill, who gave name to Tir-Con- nell, now Donegal; Cairbre, Enna, and others of inferior note, collectively forming the Northern Hy Neill.
